children.innerHTML: Each shape on this map is a flashcard, meaning it had a front and a backside.
You can flip a card by clicking the triangle that will appear after you clicked a shape.

attrs.style: font-family: "Arial Black"; color: rgb(76, 54, 51); margin-top: 17px; border-width: 2px; border-style: solid none;

children.innerHTML: You can activate Study mode (from the Options menu on the left)
In the study mode, you only have to click a shape, to flash it
After activating study mode, the study mode menu will also appear with additional options:
You can randomly show each flascards while hiding others: just press start in the one-by-one tab
You can type in answers and have Breakdown check it: just check the check checkbox, and then press start
You can flip all the cards: see the button labelled flip all
Making flashcards is easy with Breakdown Notes!
You can read all about making these flashcards at:
